CEZ Says Supervisory Board Member Ales Klepek Resigns

-- B y   L a d k a   B a u e r o v a
-- 
2011-09-16T07:53:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/cez-says-supervisory-board-member-ales-klepek-resigns.html
CEZ AS (CEZ) ’s supervisory board member
Ales Klepek resigned from his position, the Prague-based utility
said in a statement on its website.  Klepek’s resignation follows yesterday’s departure of
Martin Roman from his post as chief executive officer and
chairman of the company. Roman was named chairman of the
supervisory board yesterday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ladka Bauerova at 
 lbauerova@bloomberg.net  